00:18:40.680 --> 00:18:44.830
OK, the city is divided
into 32 districts.

00:18:44.830 --> 00:18:48.160
One of the questions was, why
are the districts so weird?

00:18:48.160 --> 00:18:51.310
Why don't they just
make them according

00:18:51.310 --> 00:18:53.260
to the voting districts?

00:18:53.260 --> 00:18:56.770
The answer is buried in history.

00:18:56.770 --> 00:19:02.230
The districts were
set up in 1969

00:19:02.230 --> 00:19:04.945
as part of an experiment
in community control.

00:19:09.670 --> 00:19:11.429
They're all set up
for political reasons.

00:19:11.429 --> 00:19:13.720
Some of them were designed
to keep all the white people

00:19:13.720 --> 00:19:14.230
together.

00:19:14.230 --> 00:19:19.300
Some of them were designed
to give Puerto Ricans

00:19:19.300 --> 00:19:21.610
power in East Harlem.

00:19:21.610 --> 00:19:25.100
Some of them were designed to
dilute African-American power.

00:19:25.100 --> 00:19:26.950
Some of them were
designed to concentrate

00:19:26.950 --> 00:19:28.820
African-American power.

00:19:28.820 --> 00:19:31.810
The reason you need to
know about them today

00:19:31.810 --> 00:19:34.990
is that your child is
guaranteed a seat in one

00:19:34.990 --> 00:19:37.510
of these in the district
in which you live.

00:19:37.510 --> 00:19:39.520
And some of the districts
are really first rate,

00:19:39.520 --> 00:19:44.530
and some of them are not
ready for prime time.

