00:36:10.310 --> 00:36:13.340
But I've looked
at School Digger,

00:36:13.340 --> 00:36:15.894
and the ranks aren't good.

00:36:15.894 --> 00:36:17.310
CLARA HEMPHILL:
What's the school?

00:36:17.310 --> 00:36:18.576
AUDIENCE: Alfred Aux.

00:36:18.576 --> 00:36:20.450
CLARA HEMPHILL: OK, I
know that school, yeah.

00:36:20.450 --> 00:36:22.400
AUDIENCE: I mean,
my kids are four.

00:36:22.400 --> 00:36:24.066
They're already signed
up for preschool,

00:36:24.066 --> 00:36:26.210
but I'm thinking about
kindergarten for years

00:36:26.210 --> 00:36:27.290
down the road.

00:36:27.290 --> 00:36:29.060
Realistically, are
there things that I

00:36:29.060 --> 00:36:31.880
can do as a parent who wants
to be involved to really make

00:36:31.880 --> 00:36:34.030
an impact on the school nearby?

00:36:34.030 --> 00:36:36.184
Or is my time better
spent thinking about

00:36:36.184 --> 00:36:38.100
how I can get my kids
into a different school,

00:36:38.100 --> 00:36:40.490
whether that's the non-zoned
district school, or moving,

00:36:40.490 --> 00:36:41.480
or something else?

00:36:41.480 --> 00:36:43.021
CLARA HEMPHILL: I
love that question.

00:36:43.021 --> 00:36:45.170
That's a really good one.

00:36:45.170 --> 00:36:47.231
Yes parents can
make a difference.

00:36:52.490 --> 00:36:58.006
You have to talk
to other parents

00:36:58.006 --> 00:37:00.380
and see if you've got other
people who can work with you.

00:37:00.380 --> 00:37:02.130
And then you have to
talk to the principal

00:37:02.130 --> 00:37:03.980
and see if he wants you to work.

00:37:03.980 --> 00:37:06.299
And you can't say,
this a terrible school.

00:37:06.299 --> 00:37:08.090
We're going to save
you and make it better.

00:37:08.090 --> 00:37:11.586
For some reason, that approach
is not really welcomed.

00:37:11.586 --> 00:37:12.710
AUDIENCE: I don't know why.

00:37:12.710 --> 00:37:14.010
CLARA HEMPHILL: But, you
know, we love the school

00:37:14.010 --> 00:37:15.093
and we want to support it.

00:37:15.093 --> 00:37:16.496
Can we do x, y, z?

00:37:19.280 --> 00:37:24.170
So some of the districts have
district-wide school choice.

00:37:24.170 --> 00:37:27.470
So again, this is
Hell's Kitchen.

00:37:27.470 --> 00:37:29.140
AUDIENCE: Yeah, 212 is right by.

00:37:29.140 --> 00:37:30.650
CLARA HEMPHILL:
Yeah, and there's

00:37:30.650 --> 00:37:34.280
Midtown West, which is a
school that accepts kids

00:37:34.280 --> 00:37:40.144
from all over the district,
and supposedly by lottery.

00:37:40.144 --> 00:37:42.560
Same as-- I don't know if you
read the piece in the Sunday

00:37:42.560 --> 00:37:45.820
"Times" about 165 and
Manhattan School for Children

00:37:45.820 --> 00:37:47.870
on the Upper West
Side, another case

00:37:47.870 --> 00:37:51.290
of a sort of
unfavored zoned school

00:37:51.290 --> 00:37:55.970
and a favored cool,
groovy, boutique, hipster,

00:37:55.970 --> 00:37:58.670
millennium school.

00:37:58.670 --> 00:38:03.890
And how they got
set up was parents

00:38:03.890 --> 00:38:05.540
who were zoned for
the unfavored school

00:38:05.540 --> 00:38:10.040
were dissatisfied and
created something new

00:38:10.040 --> 00:38:13.220
under the auspices of
the Department of Ed.

00:38:13.220 --> 00:38:22.560
And these district schools
used to have their thumb

00:38:22.560 --> 00:38:25.620
on the scales for parents
who wanted to volunteer.

00:38:25.620 --> 00:38:27.420
The last administration,
Bloomberg

00:38:27.420 --> 00:38:30.210
thought that was
not really fair.

00:38:30.210 --> 00:38:33.240
I think there was one--

00:38:33.240 --> 00:38:34.920
Joel Klein, the
previous chancellor,

00:38:34.920 --> 00:38:37.020
may have read in my
book where I said

00:38:37.020 --> 00:38:40.860
one family had two mothers,
and they promised two mothers

00:38:40.860 --> 00:38:44.040
in the PTA, and that got
them into the school.

00:38:44.040 --> 00:38:46.560
And the school's
chancellor thought

00:38:46.560 --> 00:38:49.140
this kind of string pulling
was really not very nice.

00:38:49.140 --> 00:38:51.510
So he made it everything's
done by lottery now.

00:38:51.510 --> 00:38:57.690
However, after the first
round of admissions comes out,

00:38:57.690 --> 00:39:00.060
the admissions reverts
to the local school.

00:39:00.060 --> 00:39:03.240
And at that point,
pleasant persistence

00:39:03.240 --> 00:39:07.140
can make a difference.

00:39:07.140 --> 00:39:11.820
111, your school, I
didn't put it in the book,

00:39:11.820 --> 00:39:14.060
but it's moving in
the right direction.

00:39:14.060 --> 00:39:16.290
So I would give
it another visit.

00:39:16.290 --> 00:39:19.680
And I also want to encourage
you to go to insideschools.org

00:39:19.680 --> 00:39:22.611
and not School Digger
and, you know--

00:39:22.611 --> 00:39:23.361
AUDIENCE: Will do.

00:39:23.361 --> 00:39:26.007
Thank you.

